children.name: MWG-001 Generic Parse
children.searchQuery:
_sourceCategory=$$McAfeeWebGateway mwg 
| extract "\:\d{2} (?<device>.*?) mwg"
| parse "[*] \"*\" * * * * * \"*" as date,auth_user,src_ip,dest_ip,f1,status_code,cache_status,req_line nodrop
| parse field=req_line "*\" \"*\" \"*\" \"*\" * * \"*\" \"*\" \"*\" \"*\" \"*\" \"*\" \"*\" \"*\"" as req_line, category, rep_level, media, orig_bytes, resp_bytes, user_agent, referer, evt_id, f2, f3, country, app, f4 nodrop

children.name: MWG-002 Top 50 Failed Status
children.searchQuery:
_sourceCategory=$$McAfeeWebGateway mwg 
| extract "\:\d{2} (?<device>.*?) mwg"
| parse "[*] \"*\" * * * * * \"*" as date,auth_user,src_ip,dest_ip,f1,status_code,cache_status,req_line nodrop
| parse field=req_line "*\" \"*\" \"*\" \"*\" * * \"*\" \"*\" \"*\" \"*\" \"*\" \"*\" \"*\" \"*\"" as req_line, category, rep_level, media, orig_bytes, resp_bytes, user_agent, referer, evt_id, f2, f3, country, app, f4 nodrop
| where (status_code matches "4*" or status_code matches "5*")   
| count status_code, src_ip, dest_ip, req_line
| sort _count 
| limit 50

children.name: MWG-003 High risk destinations
children.description: Requests with sources to high risk destinations
children.searchQuery:
_sourceCategory=$$McAfeeWebGateway mwg "High Risk"
| extract "\:\d{2} (?<device>.*?) mwg"
| parse "[*] \"*\" * * * * * \"*" as date,auth_user,src_ip,dest_ip,f1,status_code,cache_status,req_line nodrop
| parse field=req_line "*\" \"*\" \"*\" \"*\" * * \"*\" \"*\" \"*\" \"*\" \"*\" \"*\" \"*\" \"*\"" as req_line, category, rep_level, media, orig_bytes, resp_bytes, user_agent, referer, evt_id, f2, f3, country, app, f4 nodrop
| lookup longitude, latitude, city, region, country_name from geo://default on ip=dest_ip
| count rep_level, auth_user, src_ip, dest_ip, city, region, country_name, longitude, latitude
| sort _count

children.name: MWG-004 Request beyond minimal risk
children.searchQuery:
_sourceCategory=$$McAfeeWebGateway mwg !"Minimal Risk"
| extract "\:\d{2} (?<device>.*?) mwg"
| parse "[*] \"*\" * * * * * \"*" as date,auth_user,src_ip,dest_ip,f1,status_code,cache_status,req_line nodrop
| parse field=req_line "*\" \"*\" \"*\" \"*\" * * \"*\" \"*\" \"*\" \"*\" \"*\" \"*\" \"*\" \"*\"" as req_line, category, rep_level, media, orig_bytes, resp_bytes, user_agent, referer, evt_id, f2, f3, country, app, f4 nodrop
| count rep_level 
| sort _count

children.name: MWG-005 Huge Request Lines
children.description: These request header is very big.  Potential on URL buffer attacks.
children.searchQuery:
_sourceCategory=$$McAfeeWebGateway mwg 
| where _size=2048
| extract "\:\d{2} (?<device>.*?) mwg"
| parse "[*] \"*\" * * * * * \"*" as date,auth_user,src_ip,dest_ip,f1,status_code,cache_status,req_line nodrop
| parse field=req_line "* *?" as method, url
| lookup longitude, latitude, city, region, country_name from geo://default on ip=dest_ip
| count auth_user, src_ip, dest_ip, city, region, country_name, url, longitude, latitude 
| sort _count
| limit 50

children.name: MWG-006 Users with Multiple Source IP
children.description: Users with more than one source IP address.
children.searchQuery:
_sourceCategory=$$McAfeeWebGateway mwg  
| parse "[*] \"*\" * * * * * \"*" as date,auth_user,src_ip,dest_ip,f1,status_code,cache_status,req_line nodrop
| where !(auth_user matches "-" or auth_user matches "(*" or auth_user matches "Bypass*" or auth_user matches "system" or auth_user matches "*network*")
| count auth_user, src_ip 
| count_distinct(src_ip) by auth_user | where _count_distinct > 1 | sort _count_distinct

children.name: MWG-007 IP Address Used by Multiple People
children.description: IP address used by multiple people
children.searchQuery:
_sourceCategory=$$McAfeeWebGateway mwg
| parse "[*] \"*\" * * * * * \"*" as date,auth_user,src_ip,dest_ip,f1,status_code,cache_status,req_line nodrop
| where !(auth_user matches "-" or auth_user matches "(*" or auth_user matches "Bypass*" or auth_user matches "system" or auth_user matches "*network*")
| count auth_user, src_ip 
| count_distinct(auth_user) by src_ip | where _count_distinct > 1 | sort _count_distinct

panels.name: Top 50 Success Requests Outside of US
panels.queryString:
_sourceCategory=$$McAfeeWebGateway mwg 
| extract "\:\d{2} (?<device>.*?) mwg"
| parse "[*] \"*\" * * * * * \"*" as date,auth_user,src_ip,dest_ip,f1,status_code,cache_status,req_line nodrop
| parse field=req_line "*\" \"*\" \"*\" \"*\" * * \"*\" \"*\" \"*\" \"*\" \"*\" \"*\" \"*\" \"*\"" as req_line, category, rep_level, media, orig_bytes, resp_bytes, user_agent, referer, evt_id, f2, f3, country, app, f4 nodrop
| where status_code matches "2*"
| extract field=req_line "(?<req_line>\w+\s.*?)(?:\s|\?|$)" nodrop
| lookup longitude, latitude, city, country_name from geo://default on ip=dest_ip
| where !(country_name matches "United States")
| count rep_level, auth_user, src_ip, dest_ip, city, country_name, longitude, latitude
| sort _count
| Limit 50

panels.name: Top 50 Failed Status by Destination
panels.queryString:
_sourceCategory=$$McAfeeWebGateway mwg 
| extract "\:\d{2} (?<device>.*?) mwg"
| parse "[*] \"*\" * * * * * \"*" as date,auth_user,src_ip,dest_ip,f1,status_code,cache_status,req_line nodrop

| where (status_code matches "4*" or status_code matches "5*")
| extract field=req_line "(?<req_line>\w+\s.*?)(?:\s|\?|$)" nodrop
| concat("http://www.ipvoid.com/scan/",dest_ip,"/") as ipvoid   
| count status_code, src_ip, dest_ip, req_line, rep_level, ipvoid
| sort _count 
| limit 50
